<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-25-0165 </DOCNO><TEXT>Fiscal 1986 in Japan had a various start with a dramatic collapse in worldoil prices coupled with the continuing appreciation of the yen on theinternational money markets. The results was a major slump in the pricesof all forms of imported energy, including crude oil as one of the mostimportant energy import. These market trends have been so dramatic thatthey are without precedent, and the purpose of this study has thereforebeen to analyse the energy user's reactions to these market developmentsand in so doing draw up a short to medium term forecast of the energymarket and how it will progress within the next five years ahead. 15figs., 19 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>